cID=48.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://furried.freewebspace.com/bear10.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> Thats a little low for Chardok, but you should be ok if you stay at zone in/zone out. Don't even try to go any farther in.<br><br>Furried <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufurried.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Furried</A> at: 4/19/02 7:06:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1028<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 7:16:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> Hmm yeah you may have some troubles with that group. I'd also suggest sticking with the zone mobs. <br>Your highest tank is only L48 so he'll probably be taking pretty hard hits. I don't think you are going to have any luck on SBS drops hunting zone out mobs unfortunately.<br><br><br>Biz.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqjonze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqjonze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 9:20:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> Yea zone in or out would work.  The front fort can be tough.  A monk to help single pull and an enchanter has been needed the few times that I've gone. <p><b>Jonze</b> 56 Paladin<br><a href="http://www.eqwhitewind.com"> White Wind on Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujolith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jolith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 11:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> As mentioned above, the zone in or zone out would be the deepest this group should go until you get a few more levels under your belts. Additionally if you are going to hunt there I would highly suggest that you add some sort of a slower into your mix. Chardok mobs seem to hit fast and hard when your main tank is 48, so slow would greatly increase your chances.<br><br>The SBS does drop off mobs in the entry halls and beginning of the fort, but they are very rare from this area. Just so you know what you are getting into ahead of time. <p><table border="0" ><tr><td><table border="0"><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial"><font size="+1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4768">Jolith Halfelven</a></font></td><td><font face="arial"> - 57<SUP><FONT SIZE="-1">th</FONT></SUP> Halfelf Knight </font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial"><font size="-1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44222">Senea ap'Diancecht</a></font></td><td><font face="arial"><font size="-1"> - 55<SUP><FONT SIZE="-2">th</FONT></SUP> Barbarian Luminary</font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" align="center"><font face="arial"><a href="http://www.dolamroth.org">[ Dol Amroth ]</a> , Rodcet Nife Server</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uflintrok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flintrok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/23/02 7:28:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> May want to add and enchanter to that group...you will get adds if u try to go any further than zone in/out lines.  Have got the SBS to drop twice at the front fort (lost roll both times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) but the adds can add up without a fast group and a monk puller <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36384" target="flintrok">-=Current Profile=-</a><br><img src="http://66.197.149.109/SigPics/SigPicFlint.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uraynoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raynoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/23/02 7:32:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~suretang/images/usf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> Yeah Kinda low Lvl for Chardok,   I wouldn't leave zone in<br>if I were you.   You can get at least 6-7 Mobs at zone in and<br>if you Use pally to root the adds, or SK to pull the Mobs<br>to split em up...You can get a nice cycle going on those<br>mobs and whack em all , If you need to pull more....<br><br>You can always try to split up the fort front mobs, but I wouldn't go anywhere past fort.  Zone out is nice and all,  but the wandering and the fact if you die you have to inviso <br>or drag em to zone in...At least at zone in,  if you die..You just zone back in and corpse is there.<br><br>     Raynoc!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 935<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/23/02 8:48:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far into Chardok should this group go?</span><hr size=1> Chardok...  <br><br>I first went to Chardok at 52 or 53 with full groups of about the same level (including a damn good enchanter, my husband) .  For the longest time I was convinced it was a death trap.  We died EVERY SINGLE TIME we went. I finally refused to go back....<br><br>Now, however, your experience would be easier.... first and importantly because they changed the mobs... no more permanently sow'd sarnaks beating the hell out of you on pulls and running off to get adds if snare won't land... second because gear is so much better now (I was doing it with a mix of ro/valorium and a stave of shielding + SBS combo).... third because the introduction of +Chardok quests means non-KOS folks wander by sometimes and can help with CR / ressing.<br><br>However without crowd control or, at least, a high level slower I wouldn't go past zone in or zone out with that group. <p><a href="http://www.geocities.com/valya_w"><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/sig.gif"></a><br>Valya Wanderfoot <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94293">(Magelo)</a><br>Melliasan Sforzanda, 43 Bard <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95676">(Magelo) </a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=48.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showNextMessage?topicID=48.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=7><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.emailToFriend?topicID=48.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.threadControl?topicID=48.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=48.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=48.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><